article.headline: Long Beach St 102, UC Davis 77
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Aaron Nixon scored 27 points and Long Beach State wrapped up its non-conference schedule with a 102-77 victory over UC Davis on Saturday. Earlier in the day, Cal State Fullerton lost to Cal Poly, ensuring that the 49ers, who have three conference games remaining, will earn no worse than a tie for first in the Big West Conference. The 49ers (19-7, 9-2) who last won the conference title in 1996, will be the No. 1 seed when its tournament begins March 7. Nixon led a 15-0 run by the 49ers over a three-minute span early in the second half as Long Beach State opened a 69-47 lead with 14:32 remaining. The Aggies (4-22) dropped their 10th straight and fell to the 49ers for the fifth consecutive time. Nixon went 10-of-12 from the floor and Long Beach State shot 67 percent (42-63) for the game. The 49ers improved to 11-1 at home this season and have won six of their last seven and 17 of 20. Kejuan Johnson scored 19 points and Kevin Houston added 19 for Long Beach State. Vince Oliver led UC Davis with 15 points and Dominic Calegari added 12 points for the Aggies, who committed 20 turnovers. Nixon was 6-of-7 in the first half and scored 18 points as the 49ers led at halftime 52-38.
